OL,3,CDriver chucks chippy tea on man in a
OL,4,Cfit of road rage
OL,6,FHe described "feeling the hot curry
OL,7,Fsauce on his neck" following the
OL,8,Fassault and was forced to pull over as
OL,9,Fhe was "covered in food".
OL,11,FLloyd was then said to have begun
OL,12,Ftrying to punch him and subsequently
OL,13,Ftackled him to the ground after both
OL,14,Fmen got of of their vehicles. However,
OL,15,Fhe was cleared of a count of assault
OL,16,Foccasioning actual bodily harm in
OL,17,Frelation to this part of the incident.
OL,18,FHe then drove away "in such a hurry"
OL,19,Fthat he left his shoes and sunglasses
OL,20,Fbehind.
