OL,3,CDriver chucks chippy tea on man in a
OL,4,Cfit of road rage
OL,6,FHe also said he pushed him away in
OL,7,Fself-defence after he "came at him".
OL,8,FMr Reeve was unable to continue
OL,9,Fworking for the rest of the day as a
OL,10,Fresult of the attack. His van was also
OL,11,Funusable for several weeks.JLloyd has
OL,12,Fno previous convictions. Cheryl
OL,13,FMottram, defending, told the court
OL,14,Fthis morning, Friday: "He is a
OL,15,Fpleasant and polite man ordinarily.
OL,16,F"He accepts the verdict of the jury.
OL,17,FHe accepts that what he has done needs
OL,18,Fto be marked."JLloyd was convicted of
OL,19,Fassault by a jury and was given a 12-
OL,20,Fmonth community order with 180 hours
OL,21,Fof unpaid work and a rehabilitation
OL,22,Factivity requirement of up to 20 days.
